==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trias
<hw>Tri"as</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., triad. See
<er>Triad</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The formation situated
between the Permian and Lias, and so named by the Germans, because
consisting of three series of strata, which are called in German the
<xex>Bunter sandstein</xex>, <xex>Muschelkalk</xex>, and
<xex>Keuper</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triassic</ent>⟦br⟧
